      "content": {
        "title": "Flexor Tendon Injuries and Repair — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Laceration or rupture of flexor digitorum and flexor pollicis longus tendons within the fibro-osseous sheath.",
        "summary": "Zone II (no man's land) repairs require core and epitendinous sutures. Early protected motion protocols reduce adhesions."
      },
